dct_title_s: Germany / compiled and drawn in the Cartographic Division of the National Geographic Society for the National geographic magazine ; James M. Darley, chief cartographer.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by shading and spot heights. Depths shown by soundings. "Atlas plate 35, June 1959." Ancillary map: Berlin, Shows the "western edge of Berlin was transferred to Soviet occupation in 1945 in exchange for part of Gatow Airport transferred to British occupation".
